# API Route Conventions

## Structure

Every route handler file should follow this pattern:

1. Imports (auth, models, Zod schemas, db connection)
2. Zod validation schema(s) for request body
3. Route handler functions (GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE)

## Auth Check

```typescript
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth";

export async function GET() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session?.user) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: { code: "UNAUTHORIZED", message: "Not authenticated" } },
      { status: 401 }
    );
  }
  // ...
}
```

## Cron Route Protection

Cron routes must verify the `CRON_SECRET` header:

```typescript
if (req.headers.get("x-cron-secret") !== process.env.CRON_SECRET) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: { code: "UNAUTHORIZED" } }, { status: 401 });
}
```

## Database

Always await `dbConnect()` before any Mongoose operation:

```typescript
import { dbConnect } from "@/lib/db/mongoose";

export async function GET() {
  await dbConnect();
  const groups = await Group.find({ admin: session.user.id });
  // ...
}
```
